{"title_page": "G\u00fcig\u00fce", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name = G\u00fcig\u00fce\n|nickname = \n|motto = \n|image_skyline = \n|image_caption = \n|image_flag = \n|image_shield = \n| pushpin_map             = Venezuela\n|subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n|subdivision_type1 = [[States of Venezuela|State]]\n|subdivision_type2 = [[Municipalities of Venezuela|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flagicon|Venezuela}}[[Venezuela]]\n|subdivision_name1 = [[Carabobo]]\n|subdivision_name2 = [[Carlos Arvelo Municipality]]\n|established_title = Founded\n|established_date = 1724\n|established_title2 = \n|established_date2 = \n|government_type = [[Mayor\u2013council government|Mayor\u2013council]]\n| governing_body = Parroquia G\u00fcig\u00fce\n|leader_title =Mayor\n|leader_name  =\tYorman Alvarado<ref>{{cite web |url= http://ciudadvalencia.com.ve/alcaldes-de-carabobo-resultados/|title= Estos son los 14 alcaldes de Carabobo (+lista)}}</ref> ([[PSUV]])  \n|area_total_km2 = 114\n|population_as_of = 2005\n|population_footnotes = \n|population_total = 60000\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|timezone = [[Venezuelan Standard Time Zone|VST]]\n|utc_offset = \n|timezone_DST = \n|utc_offset_DST = \n|coordinates       = {{coord|10|05|N|67|47|W|region:VE|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes=\n|elevation_m = 667\n|population_blank1_title = \n|population_blank1 = \n|area_code = \n|postal_code_type = \n|postal_code =\n|blank1_name = [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|Climate]]\n|blank1_info = [[Tropical savanna climate|Aw]]\n|website = [http://www.alcaldiadecarlosarvelo.gob.ve/municipio-guigue/ alcaldiadecarlosarvelo.gob.ve]\n|footnotes = \n }}\n'''G\u00fcig\u00fce''' (pronounced Gwigwe) is a city in the south of the [[Valencia Lake]], in [[Carabobo]], [[Venezuela]]. It is the capital of the [[Carlos Arvelo Municipality]] and of the G\u00fcig\u00fce parish. The [[G\u00fcig\u00fce River]] flows through the city, draining in Lake Valencia.\n\n[[Image:Guigueencarabobo.jpg|thumb|right|250px|G\u00fcig\u00fce in Carabobo]]\n\n==Etymology==\nAccording to the Venezuelan polygraph [[Lisandro Alvarado|Dr. Lisandro Alvarado]], the etymology of G\u00fcig\u00fce comes from the indigenous Caribbean toponymy \"UIUE\", which means axe, or [[Thunderstone (folklore)|thunderstone]], origin attributable to the indigenous people of the contours of the Lake of Tacarigua or Valencia<ref name=h >{{cite web|title=G\u00dcIG\u00dcE PARISH|url=http://www.alcaldiadecarlosarvelo.gob.ve/municipio-guigue/|access-date=2018-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212153600/http://www.alcaldiadecarlosarvelo.gob.ve/municipio-guigue/|archive-date=2018-02-12|url-status=dead}}</ref>.\n\n== History ==\nThe origin G\u00fcig\u00fce, until now, has remained uncertain, but most historians say that G\u00fcig\u00fce was founded in 1724<ref>{{cite web|title=EL PUEBLO DE GUIGUE-CARABOBO-VENEZUELA |url=http://angarita971.obolog.es/pueblo-guigue-carabobo-venezuela-2194357}}</ref>, in the church of Our Lady of Rosary the oldest book found by Bishop Mariano Mart\u00ed<ref name=ss>{{cite web|url=http://albaciudad.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Carabobo-CarlosArvelo.pdf|title=Carabobo-CarlosArvelo}}</ref> is a parish record book that was from 1724, when the parish was served by a priest named Cura Capell\u00e1n. And this book was written on its front page in calligraphy the following sentence: \"3 de mayo de 1724 en el valle de Nuestra Se\u00f1ora del Rosario de G\u00fcig\u00fce\" (''May 3rd, 1724 in the Valley of Our Lady of the Rosary of G\u00fcig\u00fce'')<ref name=ss />. On the other hand, Don Torcuato Manzo N\u00fa\u00f1ez, who in his book \"Historia del estado Carabobo\", cites that G\u00fcig\u00fce was founded in 1747<ref name=\"Historia del estado Carabobo\">Historia del estado Carabobo 1981, p. 173</ref>.\n\n== Geography ==\nG\u00fcig\u00fce is located in the central region of Venezuela in the [[Carabobo|state of Carabobo]] and it is south of lake of Valencia. 151 km southwest of [[Caracas]]. Its lowest elevation is 445 m and its highest elevation is 667 m<ref>{{cite web|title= distance|url= http://es.distancias.himmera.com/distancia_de-guigue_a_caracas_entre_mapa_carretera-18247.html|}}</ref>. The closest cities to G\u00fcig\u00fce are Tacarigua (15.3&nbsp;km west), [[San Joaqu\u00edn, Carabobo|San Joaquin]] (20.2&nbsp;km north), [[Guacara]] (23.7&nbsp;km northwest), [[Mariara]] (23.8&nbsp;km northeast), [[Valencia, Carabobo|Valencia]] (25.3&nbsp;km northwest)<ref name= g>{{cite web|title= G\u00fcig\u00fce|url=https://www.distancesto.com/coordinates/ve/guigue-latitude-longitude/history/47945.html|}}</ref>. And the nearest airports are [[Arturo Michelena International Airport]] in Valencia (17.9&nbsp;km northwest) and [[Mariscal Sucre Airport (Venezuela)|\"MYC\" Escuela Mariscal Sucre Airport]] in [[Maracay]] (23.4&nbsp;km northeast)<ref name= g />.\nThe limits of the Municipality of G\u00fcig\u00fce are, north: Lake of Valencia, with the islands El Burro, Caiguire, Otama, El Fraile. South: la serran\u00eda de Cerro Azul, east: the state of Aragua, west: the Tacarigua parish of the Carlos Arvelo municipality<ref name= h />.\n\n== Demographics ==\nAs of 2005, the urban parish of G\u00fcig\u00fce has a little bit over 60,000 inhabitants.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right;\"\n|+Historical population<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://iies.faces.ula.ve/Proyecciones_de_Poblacion/Carabobo.htm |title=Poblaci\u00f3n de Parroquias de Carabobo |access-date=2008-06-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723145454/http://iies.faces.ula.ve/Proyecciones_de_Poblacion/Carabobo.htm |archive-date=2011-07-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n! Year || Pop. || Change %\n|-\n|1990 || 45339 ||\n|-\n|1991 || 46546 || +2.7%\n|-\n|1992 || 47747 || +2.6%\n|-\n|1993 || 48940 || +2.5%\n|-\n|1994 || 50124 || +2.4%\n|-\n|1995 || 51302 || +2.4%\n|-\n|1996 || 52471 || +2.3%\n|-\n|1997 || 53631 || +2.2%\n|-\n|1998 || 54781 || +2.1%\n|-\n|1999 || 55921 || +2.1%\n|-\n|2000 || 57043 || +2.0%\n|-\n|2005 || 62464 || +9.5%\n|}\n\n== Tourism ==\n[[Image:Abad\u00eda de G\u00fcig\u00fce (Carabobo, Venezuela).jpg|thumb|right|300px|Benedictine church of G\u00fcig\u00fce]]\n\n* [[Abbey of G\u00fcig\u00fce|Benedictine Abbey of Saint Joseph]], G\u00fcig\u00fce: this monastery is famous for its architecture as well as its Gregorian chants and the agricultural products it offers.\n* Plaza Arvelo and Chapel of the Savior of the World, it has the bronze bust of the eponymous, inaugurated in October 1962, on the occasion of the centenary of the death of Carlos Arvelo. In the temple located in front of it, contains the adolescent image of Jesus, Salvador del Mundo (Savior of the world), he is celebrated on January 1st of each year<ref name= h />.\n*Casa de la Cultura, Cultural building, where there is the artistic pictures of local painters and painters from the central region of Venezuela<ref name= h />. But lately it's been discovered that \"Casa de la Cultura\" is abandoned since it's not being funded or getting aid from the municipality of Carlos Arvelo even though a meeting was arranged between Leonardo Crociata, president of the cultural institution and Ra\u00fal Bracamonte, mayor of Carlos Arvelo where he said that in the talks it was agreed to grant due encouragement to the arts and culture. Plus props, furniture, paint materials have been stolen<ref>{{cite web|title=Carlos Arvelo: Casa de la Cultura de G\u00fcig\u00fce se encuentra abandonada |url=https://www.el-carabobeno.com/Carlos-Arvelo-Casa-de-la-Cultura-de-Guigue-se-encuentra-abandonada/|}}</ref>.\n\n== Notable people from G\u00fcig\u00fce ==\n* [[Carlos Arvelo| Dr. Carlos Arvelo]] - Military Surgeon\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Guigue}}\n[[Category:Cities in Carabobo]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1724]]\n[[Category:1724 establishments in the Spanish Empire]]\n", "t