{"title_page": "Ciar\u00e1n Griffiths", "text_new": "{{short description|British  actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Ciar\u00e1n Griffiths\n| image =\n| imagesize = \n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|3|3}}\n| birth_place = [[Manchester]], [[England]], [[UK]]\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 1998\u2013present\n| High School Attended = St Mary's Catholic High School, Astley, Manchester.\n| death_date =\n| birth_name = Ciar\u00e1n Joseph Griffiths<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.ancestry.co.uk/iexec/?htx=view&r=5538&dbid=8964&iid=ONS_B19831AZ-0597&fn=&ln=Record+from+England+%26+Wales%2c+Birth+Index%3a+1837-1983&st=d&ssrc=&pid=781745|title=GRO Birth Registration Index|accessdate=2006-11-12|publisher=Ancestry.co.uk}}{{Dead link|date=November 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| othername =\n| homepage =\n|}}\n'''Ciar\u00e1n Joseph Griffiths''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|k|\u026a\u0259r|\u0259|n}}; born 3 March 1983; [[Manchester]], England) is an English [[actor]], best known for his roles as [[Gary Best]] in ''[[The Bill]]'' and [[Mickey Maguire (Shameless)|Micky Maguire]] in ''[[Shameless (UK TV series)|Shameless]]''. In 2018, he made a guest appearance in BBC soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]'', playing the role of [[List of EastEnders characters (2018)#Milo|Milo]] from 1 January to 2 January.\n\n==Biography==\nGriffiths attended [[St Mary's Catholic High School, Astley|St Mary's RC High School]] in [[Astley, Greater Manchester|Astley]] near [[Leigh, Greater Manchester|Leigh]], between 1994 and 1999; it was during this time that he starred in ''[[Children's Ward (UK TV series)|Children's Ward]]'' at the age of thirteen.\n\nAside from his long-running roles in ''The Bill'' and ''Shameless'', Griffiths has made guest appearances on ''[[Coronation Street]]'', ''[[Clocking Off]]'', ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' and numerous other programmes.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.hellomagazine.ca/profiles/ciarangriffiths/ | publisher=[[Hello!]] | accessdate=2009-05-16 | title=Ciaran Griffiths }}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Griffiths starred alongside Conrad Westmaas in the short film ''[[The Visitor (2007 short film)|The Visitor]]''. He also appeared as \"Psycho\" in the film ''[[There's Only One Jimmy Grimble]]''.\n\nHe also starred in the British [[vampire film]] ''[[Dead Cert (2010 film)|Dead Cert]]'' which was directed by Steven Lawson,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fangoria.com/home/news/27-international-frights/4217-more-cast-new-poster-for-vampire-film-dead-cert.html |title=More cast, new poster for vampire film DEAD CERT |access-date=8 October 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091012111456/http://www.fangoria.com/home/news/27-international-frights/4217-more-cast-new-poster-for-vampire-film-dead-cert.html |archive-date=12 October 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and he appeared in ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' as [[List of Waterloo Road characters#Series 6|Dylan Hodge]] in Series 6 in 2010/2011.\n\nIn the August 2011 issue of [[Attitude Magazine]], Griffiths took his top off and appeared sporting a red boxing kit. Photos from the shoot were taken at Cloud 23 Bar in the [[Hilton Hotel]] in Manchester.\n\nHe has also appeared in adverts, including the BT vision advert where he is featured having his hair washed.{{Citation needed|date=July 2011}} In 2016, he appeared in ''[[Vera (TV series)|Vera]]'', on [[ITV (network)|ITV]] in the episode, \"The Sea Glass\", he played the role of Steve Stonnall.\n\nOn New Year's Day 2018, Griffiths made a guest appearance in the [[BBC One]] [[soap opera]], ''[[EastEnders]]'', playing [[List of EastEnders characters (2018)#Milo|Milo]].\n\nIn 2020, Griffiths starred in an episode of the [[BBC One]] drama [[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]], as Peter Hawker, a man who\u2019d suffered a brain injury.\n\n==Filmography==\n'''Film'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[There's Only One Jimmy Grimble]]'' || Psycho ||\n|-\n| 2006 || ''To the Sea Again'' || Jack || Short film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''The Visitor'' || Jack || Short film\n|-\n| 2008 || ''Clubbed'' || Reaper ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''Ace of Grace || Robbie ||\n|-\n| 2009 || ''CGI-brows'' || Acolyte || Short film\n|-\n| 2010 || ''Just for the Record'' || Danny Allgen ||\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Dead Cert (2010 film)|Dead Cert]]'' || Skender ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Big Fat Gypsy Gangster]]'' || Carl Thompson || \n|-\n| 2012 || ''Doormen'' || Tommo || Short film\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Svengali (2013 film)|Svengali]]'' || Burnsy || TV film\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Sea View'' || Jason || Short film\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Haunted House: Exorcist'' || Father Patrick || Short film\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Rabbit Punch'' || Dylan || Short film\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Television'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[The Cops (TV series)|Stanton Blues]]'' || Ian Lillie || 1 episode\n|-\n| 1998\u20131999 || ''[[City Central (TV series)|City Central]]'' || Simon Mackey || 4 episodes\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Always and Everyone]]'' || Gary Manley || Episode: \"Always and Everyone\"\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Monsignor Renard]]'' || Company Runner || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Coronation Street]]'' || Dean Sykes|| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Emmerdale]]'' || Ben McCarthy || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Where the Heart Is (UK TV series)|Where the Heart Is]]'' || Carl Garton || Episode: \"Temptation\"\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Heartbeat (UK TV series)|Heartbeat]]'' || Vic Sands || Episode: \"No Hiding Place\"\n|-\n| 2002 || ''[[Stig of the Dump]]'' || Security Guard 1 || Episode: \"Going Home\"\n|-\n| 2002 || ''[[Clocking Off]]'' || Chris Preston || Episode: \"Alan's Story\"\n|-\n| 2002 || ''[[At Home with the Braithwaites]]'' || Tel the Fitter || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2002\u20132005 || ''[[The Bill]]'' || [[Gary Best]] || Series regular; 163 episodes\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Murder Investigation Team (TV series)|Murder Investigation Team]]'' || Gary Best || Episode: \"Moving Targets\"\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[The Street (UK TV series)|The Street]]'' || Terry || Episode: \"Football\"\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Vincent (TV series)|Vincent]]'' || Stranger / PI || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Blue Murder (UK TV series)|Blue Murder]]'' || Kevin Robertson || Episode: \"In Deep\"\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Holby City]]'' || Jem Neil || Episode: \"The Borders of Sleep\"\n|-\n| 2007\u20132012 || ''[[Shameless (UK TV series)|Shameless]]'' || [[Mickey Maguire (Shameless)|Micky Maguire]] || Series regular; 84 episodes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' || [[List of Waterloo Road characters (series 6)#Dylan Hodge|Dylan Hodge]] || 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Atlantis (TV series)|Atlantis]]'' || Cyrus || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014 || ''[[The Mill (TV series)|The Mill]]'' || Boon / Matthew Boon || Series regular; 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Moving On (TV series)|Moving On]]'' || Kev || Episode: \"Blind\"\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[This is England '90]]'' || Leon || Episode: \"Winter\"\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Vera (TV series)|Vera]]'' || Steve Stonnall || Episode: \"The Sea Glass\"\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Cold Feet (TV series)|Cold Feet]]'' ||Sean Westwood || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[EastEnders]]'' || [[List of EastEnders characters (2018)#Milo|Milo]] || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\u20132019 || ''[[Shakespeare & Hathaway: Private Investigators]]'' ||Billy Porters || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[The Bay (TV series)|The Bay]]'' || Lee Ward || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'' || Peter Hawker || 1 episode\n|}\n\n'''Video Games'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2013 || Ryse: Son of Rome|| Additional Voices || Voice\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nGriffiths is an avid supporter of [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>[http://www1.skysports.com/other-sports/news/13871/3081004/united-through-and-through \"United through and through\"]. ''[[Sky Sports]]''.</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, he announced he and his partner were expecting their first child together.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0341647|name=Ciaran Griffiths}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Griffiths, Ciaran}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Manchester]]\n\n\n{{UK-screen-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British  actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Ciar\u00e1n Griffiths\n| image =\n| imagesize = \n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|3|3}}\n| birth_place = [[Manchester]], [[England]], [[UK]]\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 1998\u2013present\n| High School Attended = St Mary's Catholic High School, Astley, Manchester.\n| death_date =\n| birth_name = Ciar\u00e1n Joseph Griffiths<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.ancestry.co.uk/iexec/?htx=view&r=5538&dbid=8964&iid=ONS_B19831AZ-0597&fn=&ln=Record+from+England+%26+Wales%2c+Birth+Index%3a+1837-1983&st=d&ssrc=&pid=781745|title=GRO Birth Registration Index|accessdate=2006-11-12|publisher=Ancestry.co.uk}}{{Dead link|date=November 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| othername =\n| homepage =\n|}}\n'''Ciar\u00e1n Joseph Griffiths''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|k|\u026a\u0259r|\u0259|n}}; born 3 March 1983; [[Manchester]], England) is an English [[actor]], best known for his roles as [[Gary Best]] in ''[[The Bill]]'' and [[Mickey Maguire (Shameless)|Micky Maguire]] in ''[[Shameless (UK TV series)|Shameless]]''. In 2018, he made a guest appearance in BBC soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]'', playing the role of [[List of EastEnders characters (2018)#Milo|Milo]] from 1 January to 2 January.\n\n==Biography==\nGriffiths attended [[St Mary's Catholic High School, Astley|St Mary's RC High School]] in [[Astley, Greater Manchester|Astley]] near [[Leigh, Greater Manchester|Leigh]], between 1994 and 1999; it was during this time that he starred in ''[[Children's Ward (UK TV series)|Children's Ward]]'' at the age of thirteen.\n\nAside from his long-running roles in ''The Bill'' and ''Shameless'', Griffiths has made guest appearances on ''[[Coronation Street]]'', ''[[Clocking Off]]'', ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' and numerous other programmes.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.hellomagazine.ca/profiles/ciarangriffiths/ | publisher=[[Hello!]] | accessdate=2009-05-16 | title=Ciaran Griffiths }}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Griffiths starred alongside Conrad Westmaas in the short film ''[[The Visitor (2007 short film)|The Visitor]]''. He also appeared as \"Psycho\" in the film ''[[There's Only One Jimmy Grimble]]''.\n\nHe also starred in the British [[vampire film]] ''[[Dead Cert (2010 film)|Dead Cert]]'' which was directed by Steven Lawson,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fangoria.com/home/news/27-international-frights/4217-more-cast-new-poster-for-vampire-film-dead-cert.html |title=More cast, new poster for vampire film DEAD CERT |access-date=8 October 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091012111456/http://www.fangoria.com/home/news/27-international-frights/4217-more-cast-new-poster-for-vampire-film-dead-cert.html |archive-date=12 October 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and he appeared in ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' as [[List of Waterloo Road characters#Series 6|Dylan Hodge]] in Series 6 in 2010/2011.\n\nIn the August 2011 issue of [[Attitude Magazine]], Griffiths took his top off and appeared sporting a red boxing kit. Photos from the shoot were taken at Cloud 23 Bar in the [[Hilton Hotel]] in Manchester.\n\nHe has also appeared in adverts, including the BT vision advert where he is featured having his hair washed.{{Citation needed|date=July 2011}} In 2016, he appeared in ''[[Vera (TV series)|Vera]]'', on [[ITV (network)|ITV]] in the episode, \"The Sea Glass\", he played the role of Steve Stonnall.\n\nOn New Year's Day 2018, Griffiths made a guest appearance in the [[BBC One]] [[soap opera]], ''[[EastEnders]]'', playing [[List of EastEnders characters (2018)#Milo|Milo]].\n\nIn 2020, Griffiths starred in an episode of the [[BBC One]] drama [[Casualty]], as Peter Hawker, a man who\u2019d suffered a brain injury.\n\n==Filmography==\n'''Film'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[There's Only One Jimmy Grimble]]'' || Psycho ||\n|-\n| 2006 || ''To the Sea Again'' || Jack || Short film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''The Visitor'' || Jack || Short film\n|-\n| 2008 || ''Clubbed'' || Reaper ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''Ace of Grace || Robbie ||\n|-\n| 2009 || ''CGI-brows'' || Acolyte || Short film\n|-\n| 2010 || ''Just for the Record'' || Danny Allgen ||\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Dead Cert (2010 film)|Dead Cert]]'' || Skender ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Big Fat Gypsy Gangster]]'' || Carl Thompson || \n|-\n| 2012 || ''Doormen'' || Tommo || Short film\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Svengali (2013 film)|Svengali]]'' || Burnsy || TV film\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Sea View'' || Jason || Short film\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Haunted House: Exorcist'' || Father Patrick || Short film\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Rabbit Punch'' || Dylan || Short film\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Television'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[The Cops (TV series)|Stanton Blues]]'' || Ian Lillie || 1 episode\n|-\n| 1998\u20131999 || ''[[City Central (TV series)|City Central]]'' || Simon Mackey || 4 episodes\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Always and Everyone]]'' || Gary Manley || Episode: \"Always and Everyone\"\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Monsignor Renard]]'' || Company Runner || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Coronation Street]]'' || Dean Sykes|| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Emmerdale]]'' || Ben McCarthy || 1 episode\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Where the Heart Is (UK TV series)|Where the Heart Is]]'' || Carl Garton || Episode: \